" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:100%" class="r-1x7relf" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R5rb2:"><div data-rid="9c29514a-ec02-481e-a518-ca15f64ddd69" class="r-dfo28"><div data-rid="ab9d5612-3883-48a8-9a82-0aabce8f7a4b" class="r-1dqr3j5 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Many customers feel the difference within days — more energy, better workouts, improved stamina. For others, it can take a few weeks. The good news? You don’t have to guess. Our Nitric Oxide Test Strips let you <em>see</em> the supplement working within just 90 minutes of taking it.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="7515dd88-8e0a-4d8e-ae08-cd30fab7df18" class="r-1eqc40v" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="b8de8e6f-d60f-404a-9d28-4b4a34facde7" class="r-rx6i64" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="add8a18e-6532-46d8-b060-9710dbacda3e" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R6bb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-3xfc0s"><div data-rid="dd12321c-5c5d-4b0f-807e-c3db319d8ced" class="r-t2dtbs alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I take Berkeley Life with other medications?<br></p></span></div><div data-rid="81ef6ecd-5f92-45dd-8c59-2592ea425aa6" class="r-1gvd1u7" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:100%" class="r-1f13rrl" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R6bb2:"><div data-rid="a021c65d-2b75-44fa-b965-10584d138338" class="r-125i0jn"><div data-rid="e4c4de14-bbeb-47f5-af60-d7ddbe0b365f" class="r-9uvigj alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Yes. Berkeley Life is safe, well-tolerated, and has no known interactions with medications. Still, if you're on a specific treatment plan, it's always smart to check with your doctor.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="a94dafab-024c-4a59-afe1-a4800cc44c5c" class="r-3jmjql" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="09b2bee3-504a-4984-94de-26daab0b61db" class="r-1moivzw" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="0c739ff4-5cf6-4974-b9e4-fbb2d96ebaa0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R6rb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-o3p52g"><div data-rid="97078922-f34c-4081-bb41-3f9eed175a15" class="r-1xssjv4 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Is this product safe? Are there any side effects?</p></span></div><div data-rid="bd46b78d-1dfc-4835-a954-00105ba63147" class="r-1frfcpj" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:100%" class="r-igfzn4" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R6rb2:"><div data-rid="aa7dd92b-20f0-4d76-bac0-286c96c07b17" class="r-qhqtcw"><div data-rid="caf964cc-0d22-46f2-8846-e47e1ea7f16f" class="r-cb3ldn alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Yes, Berkeley Life’s Nitric Oxide Foundation is clinically tested and drug-free. It’s generally well-tolerated, but as with any supplement, consult your healthcare provider if you have concerns.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="eefa3a78-5ac2-4044-807a-d1cabde2acaa" class="r-1tmk38b" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="ba01d2f6-163d-4b09-824f-17c756464283" class="r-bprz0p" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="d2e919fb-41be-41ac-b92f-a13f83f9e468" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R7bb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-crfvb3"><div data-rid="f519a5e3-042e-48b4-ba16-34b86e7b36fc" class="r-cozyzp alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I get the dietary nitrates in Berkeley Life just through my diet?</p></span></div><div data-rid="affd8248-3e37-4247-a582-e3266a312fe5" class="r-1nn1rht" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:100%" class="r-151c1jh" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R7bb2:"><div data-rid="515575f7-be59-4bc7-9a4d-1fcd8c724542" class="r-1r3vgdz"><div data-rid="134e4137-cc94-4c09-b62f-a4f6f94da314" class="r-f1rjvr alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><span style="color: rgb(9, 9, 9)">Leafy greens, beetroot, arugula, spinach and celery are all vegetables known to be high in dietary nitrates. However, nutrient density of the soil across the country makes it difficult to predict exactly how much of these greens are required daily to provide a clinically effective dose of nitrates to produce nitric oxide. In our experience, it requires more leafy greens than most people over 35 are willing or able to consume every day.</span></p></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="2643e91d-3f61-4ef5-bb34-6ab22dee15fd" class="r-qlpbpa"><div data-rid="e30a1d5b-6336-422d-9605-63adc90699d3" class="r-15kef4i alchemy-rte"><span style="widt